        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:91:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/91/1",
        "text": [
          " رَجُلٍ أَعْتَقَ عَشِيَّةَ عَرَفَةَ عَبْداً لَهُ قَالَ «يُجْزِي عَنِ اَلْعَبْدِ حَجَّةُ اَلْإِسْلاَمِ وَ يُكْتَبُ لِلسَّيِّدِ أَجْرَانِ ثَوَابُ اَلْعِتْقِ وَ ثَوَابُ اَلْحَجِّ »."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.2891 - Al-Hasan ibn Mahbub narrated from Shihab, from Abu Abdullah (as), regarding a man who freed his servant on the eve of Arafah.\nImam (as) said: \"The Hajj of Islam suffices for the servant, and the master is rewarded twice: once for the act of freeing the servant and once for the reward of the Hajj.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1326,
